    "updated_at": "2024-09-01T20:45:44Z",
    "body": "> The whole prompt blinks, not only the cursor. As I wrote, I disabled the character, so I don't expect the prompt to be redrawn.\r\n\r\nI belive the reason this occurs is that when you `starship init` it overwrites the [`ViModeChangeHandler`](https://github.com/starship/starship/blob/ad705ef5529dc521806b98112f48269317125de9/src/init/starship.ps1#L214). Since that is executed last, your version gets overwritten. The `ViModeChangeHandler` (from the starship init script) does redraw the prompt when you switch modes. You can try to set your version after you load starship and see if that works the way you want.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
